<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1247,1699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,1247,1273]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Distribution</emphasis>
:—Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[652,702,1247,1273]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
locality at Chulumani, 
<collectingCountry box="[982,1071,1247,1273]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, elevation about 
<quantity box="[1273,1436,1247,1273]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.175" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.15" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="2175.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="2150.0">2150–2200 m</quantity>
in highly disturbed, montane forest. Several individuals were observed in the canopy of different tree species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1247,1699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,1324,1350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The epithet honours Dr. Stephan Beck who collected the specimen of this new species and assisted me many times with logistical and administative support in 
<collectingCountry box="[950,1040,1363,1389]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1247,1699]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,1401,1427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[367,547,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stephanii">
<emphasis box="[367,547,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis stephanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to section 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1799" box="[787,849,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,849,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is characterised by the widely spreading and equally sized sepals (
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[460,592,1441,1467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" pagination="31 - 236" refId="ref1129" refString="Luer, C. A. (2009) Icones Pleurothallidinarum XXX, Systematics of Stelis, Stelis of Ecuador, part four. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 115: 31 - 236." type="journal article" year="2009">Luer 2009</bibRefCitation>
). It may be related to the species complex of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindley (1842: 64)" authorityName="Lindley" authorityPageNumber="64" authorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentata">
<emphasis box="[1145,1334,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis argentata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lindley, J." pageId="2" pageNumber="51" pagination="64" refId="ref1061" refString="Lindley, J. (1842) Edwards Botanical Register; or, Ornamental Flower-Garden and Shrubbery. vol. 28 of the entire work or vol. 15 of the new series: 64. James Ridgway, London." type="journal article" year="1842">Lindley (1842: 64)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is documented from 
<collectingCountry box="[609,695,1479,1505]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
as well. 
<taxonomicName box="[799,977,1480,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stephanii">
<emphasis box="[799,977,1480,1505]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis stephanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from species of this complex in the triangulate lip and the partially pubescent sepals. The lip of 
<taxonomicName box="[964,1156,1518,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stephanii">
<emphasis box="[964,1156,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis stephanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unusually long and papillous, in the complex of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1842" box="[483,665,1557,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentata">
<emphasis box="[483,665,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis argentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lip is transversely subquadrate (
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[1083,1211,1556,1582]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" pagination="31 - 236" refId="ref1129" refString="Luer, C. A. (2009) Icones Pleurothallidinarum XXX, Systematics of Stelis, Stelis of Ecuador, part four. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 115: 31 - 236." type="journal article" year="2009">Luer 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In the complex of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1842" box="[151,334,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentata">
<emphasis box="[151,334,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis argentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the hairs are on the whole sepal or absent and shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1135,1313,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stephanii">
<emphasis box="[1135,1313,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis stephanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which are there only on the margins of the sepals. With its total height of about 
<quantity box="[972,1092,1634,1660]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" unit="cm" value="17.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="14.0">14–20 cm</quantity>
, the new species is relatively large for the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1799" box="[376,439,1673,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[376,439,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swartz" authorityYear="1799" box="[721,784,1673,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Stelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,784,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Stelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
size can vary markedly.
</paragraph>
